HEADWORD: Macrura
<hw>Ma*cru"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ long + <?/ tail.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A subdivision of
decapod Crustacea, having the abdomen largely developed. It includes the
lobster, prawn, shrimp, and many similar forms. Cf.
<er>Decapoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
